<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy" %>

<section class="bg-gray-950 min-h-screen">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-white tracking-tight">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-400">Effective April 28, 2026</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed text-[15px]">
      <p>
        Agent 44 Labs ("Agent 44 Labs", "we", "us") builds tools that let small
        businesses run AI agents to monitor, test, and post on their behalf.
        This policy explains what we collect, why, and what we do with it.
      </p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">What we collect</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc list-outside pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><strong class="text-white">Account information</strong> — your
            email address, an optional display name, and a hashed password
            (we never store passwords in plain text).</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Sign-in data</strong> — when you sign
            in we record the session's IP address and user-agent so you can
            see and revoke active sessions. If you enable Face ID, the
            credential lives in your device's keychain — it never leaves your
            phone.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Push notification tokens</strong> —
            if you opt into push notifications we store your device's APNs
            token so Apple's servers can deliver alerts to your phone.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Usage analytics</strong> — pages you
            view inside the app (path, referrer, browser, device type) and
            counts of features you've used (e.g. AI-enhanced posts). This is
            used for our internal product analytics dashboard.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Coarse location</strong> — we infer
            an approximate city/region from your IP address (server-side, via
            ip-api.com) for analytics. We do not request GPS location from
            your device.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">What we don't collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do not collect health data, financial data, your contacts,
          precise (GPS) location, browsing history outside the app, search
          history, advertising identifiers, or crash diagnostics. We do not
          run third-party analytics SDKs (no Google Analytics, Facebook SDK,
          Mixpanel, Segment, etc.). We do not track you across other apps or
          websites.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">How we use what we collect</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc list-outside pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li>To create and authenticate your account.</li>
          <li>To deliver push notifications you've subscribed to.</li>
          <li>To send transactional emails (verification, password resets).</li>
          <li>To improve the product through internal analytics.</li>
          <li>To generate AI-enhanced content when you explicitly request it.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Third parties</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We rely on a small number of service providers to operate the app:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc list-outside pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><strong class="text-white">Anthropic (Claude API)</strong> —
            when you use AI-enhancement features, the content you're enhancing
            (e.g. event details) is sent to Anthropic for processing. We do
            not send your email, name, or other account identifiers.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Apple Push Notification service</strong> —
            for delivering push notifications to your device.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Brevo</strong> — for sending
            transactional email (your address is shared so we can email you).</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">ip-api.com</strong> — for the
            server-side IP-to-city lookup used by analytics.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-white">Fly.io</strong> — our application
            hosting provider.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do not sell your data, share it with data brokers, or use it for
          targeted advertising.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Retention</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Account data is retained while your account is active. If you
          delete your account, we delete your account record and associated
          push tokens and sessions. Aggregate analytics may be retained in
          de-identified form.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Your rights</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You can request access to your data, correct it, or delete it by
          emailing us at the address below. If you're in a jurisdiction with
          additional rights (e.g. EU/UK GDPR, California CCPA/CPRA), those
          rights apply.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Children</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Agent 44 Labs is not directed to children under 13. We do not
          knowingly collect personal information from children under 13.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Changes</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If we make material changes to this policy we'll update the
          effective date at the top and, where appropriate, notify you in the
          app or by email.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Questions, requests, or feedback:
          <a href="mailto:botwhisperer@hey.com" class="text-orange-400 hover:text-orange-300 underline underline-offset-2">botwhisperer@hey.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
